<h2 dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;text-align: center;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:11pt;">The National Trust of Georgia, with the support of the British Embassy, announces the contest “My Heritage” for citizens of Georgia</h2><p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 11pt;">The aim of the contest is to promote and raise public awareness of individuals who share a deep appreciation for heritage and recognize the need for its preservation and promotion as a tangible expression of national identity and creativity</p><h2 dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;"><img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXepZFeAxkp57AnNui1PbRkwPhVDOT9_noLeW_E3BcZBSNB8fLIebRCoARNZqsbgwqF5hCNOT5zeABePkVujAJAX-PxKmTkXnqooG15g5COojnOepCkoSK1B5SDjJpW9uzZGxClo?key=67sU6XThS6SBacXsscln0A" width="624" height="780"></h2><h2 align="center"><p data-start="94" data-end="230"><b style="font-weight:normal;" id="docs-internal-guid-422a8b09-7fff-bea7-a9f0-c1c84ef49a5b"><br></b></p></h2><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:11pt;">If you care for, protect, and preserve Georgia’s cultural heritage, you are welcome to participate in the contest. Winners will receive minor cash prizes.<br>If you are interested, please fill out the contest application form between March 27 and April 19 via the following link:<br><br>🔗 <a href="https://forms.gle/APkPPWhLxu4qgFDs7">Application form</a><a href="https://forms.gle/APkPPWhLxu4qgFDs7" style="text-decoration:none;"><br><br></a>The “My Heritage” contest includes four categories:<br></p><ol><li><b>Preservation, adaptation, or conservation of a building or its part;</b></li><li><b>Restoration and preservation of movable cultural heritage items, such as artworks on canvas, paper, or wood, as well as items made of glass, ceramic, metal, textiles, and other materials;</b></li><li><b>Preservation and sharing of traditional crafts, materials, artisanal skills, or recipes;</b></li><li><b>Preservation, research, and transmission of traditional knowledge, folklore, oral histories, or family traditions.</b></li></ol><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:11pt;">We will provide more detailed information about each category in upcoming posts.<br>The winners will be selected by a jury composed of professionals working in the field of cultural heritage. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted no later than April 25.<br>If you have any questions, feel free to send us a direct message or call us at +995 555 49 09 17.</p><p></p><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:11pt;"><i>The “My Heritage” contest was first launched by the National Trust of Georgia in 2019 with the support of the British Embassy. Past winners included residents from Racha, Samtskhe-Javakheti, and Kakheti regions.</i></p>